# Cursor Rules тАФ How to Use

## Two tiers
- **Team rules** (`team-rules/`) тАФ org standards. MUST comply **when present**; not every repo has them.
- **Workspace rules** (this folder, except `team-rules/`) тАФ modes, monorepo map, quality bar.

Load `team-rules/` and `@project-context` only if they exist in this workspace. If absent, follow the **Non-negotiables** below and match the edited file's existing style.

## Before any code change
1. Match existing style in the file you edit; apply team rules (if present) to new/changed code only.
2. Cross-repo or unfamiliar project тЖТ `@project-context` first (if present).
3. Design тЖТ `@planning`. Bug тЖТ `@bug_investigation` then `@bug_fix`.
4. User asks / wants copy-paste fix тЖТ `@ask_mode`. Agent will build a prompt тЖТ `@build_agent_prompt`; agent will implement тЖТ `@agent_mode`. Unclear тЖТ ask one question first. After 2тАУ3 unresolved exchanges тЖТ offer Re-Ask Prompt from `ask_mode.mdc`.
5. UI / templates / CSS тЖТ `@theme` (cozy palette, Tailwind tokens тАФ no ad-hoc colors).

## Team rules (if present тАФ full detail; invoke or let modes pull them in)
| File | Covers |
|------|--------|
| `team-rules/conventions.mdc` | formatting, logging, docstrings, HTTPStatus |
| `team-rules/rules.mdc` | Pydantic, data-model, globals, unittest |
| `team-rules/security.mdc` | input validation, path traversal, clean/dirty zones |

## Workspace modes
| @name | When |
|-------|------|
| `@planning` | design before code |
| `@write_new_code` | new feature/module |
| `@bug_investigation` / `@bug_fix` | bugs |
| `@code_review` | PR review |
| `@architecture` | layer boundaries, new service/stage |
| `@code_quality` | readable/clean code, refactor, quality review тАФ or `@write_new_code` / `@code_review` |
| `@project-context` | 77-repo navigation (if present) |
| `@build_agent_prompt` | build copy-paste agent prompt тАФ agent will implement |
| `@agent_mode` | agent implements an approved task/prompt тАФ verify, conform, stage, report |
| `@ask_mode` | direct answer / copy-paste fix тАФ user implements themselves |
| `@perspectives` | open Q&A, discussions, trade-offs |
| `@test_writing` | writing or adding tests |
| `@theme` | UI/HTML/CSS тАФ cozy palette, Tailwind tokens, RTL layout |

## Open questions & discussions
When exploring, comparing options, or asking for opinion (not implementing yet):
1. Pick 1тАУ3 roles from `perspectives.mdc` тАФ state them at the top.
2. Answer substantively; surface role tensions if they disagree.
3. End with the **Opinion** block from `perspectives.mdc`.

For implementation tasks, use the relevant `@` mode instead of the Opinion block unless the user also asks for a review lens.

## Non-negotiables (always тАФ compressed; see team-rules/ if present for full detail)
- Type hints, Sphinx docstrings, `logging` not `print`, `HTTPStatus` not bare ints
- Pydantic / data-model for JSON; no mutable module globals
- Path traversal protection; no stack traces to external callers
- Reuse existing code; smallest change that solves the task
